date: stated on April 1, 2019 in a Facebook post:
title: No, Muller's report didn't leak.
text: If we often feel like April's stupid day here in Politi Fuckett, we check a lot of Facebook fliers that invent quotations or transmit false news. Today is no different. A new article we first saw on April 1 has people wondering whether Robert Mueller's private attorney's investigation has been leaked. "CBS, CNN Report that Muller's full report has been leaked," reads the text of the postage accompanying the image of what resembles the first page of an official federal document, complete with the seal of the Ministry of Justice, and entitled "Report of the Special Adviser's investigation into Russian intervention during and before the 2016 presidential election." This post, which was posted on the Facebook page San Diego Rostra on 1 April, was featured as part of Facebook efforts to combat false news and misinformation in the news broadcast. ∙ (Read more about our partnership with Facebook.) We have not been able to find any coverage for leaking a report to CBS and CNN sites. However, after a Facebook link leads to a story on the site of San Diego Rostra, where the authors of the site and external contributors publish their opinions. The story, written by the site manager under the name "Agent Thor," provides a link to the report, which says "Anonymous source has been loaded." Anyone who hopes to receive details of Mueller's thoughts on allegations that President Donald Trump has impeded justice will be disappointed. "Report" does not mention obstruction, Russia or even Trump. Instead, you'll find the words "All the Stars," the 1999 Smash Mouth song. Facebook was published on January 11, 2021 in Facebook, Nancy Belusi, who was no longer the Speaker of the House of Representatives by Samantha Buterman.
